Queues Backlog Tab

The Queues Backlog tab is shown if either queue-based routing or external routing for Omni-Channel is enabled in your org.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs), Lightning Experience
Omni Supervisor is available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

Use the Queues Summary view to catch up on activity in your Omni-Channel queues. See priority, configured work size, type, and wait times. This information can help you determine which queues are doing well and which could use more agents.

To change the agents assigned to queues, select the queues and click Assign Agents. The Queue Details view drills into specific queues so you can see their configurations, available agents, wait times, and work items.
